<h1>Keith Kritselis</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.keithkritselis.com/now.html">keithkritselis.com/now.html</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Austin
TX
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
I am a full-time UX Prototyper at Dell.com, a part-time Web Development instructor for ConsultingSolutions.net, and President of the newly formed K&T Manufacturing, LLC where I am designing and manufacturing a line of Tessellating Cookie Cutters.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I learn, I make, and I teach.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I live for that "Aha!" moment.  It's the reason I stay up till 2am, and the reason I get up at 6am.  I get that Aha moment when I find a new insight into how the world works, and the next best thing is when I can provide that moment for my students.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
The smartest guy in the world does dumb shit all the time.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
"Understanding Comics" by Scott McCloud
</p>

